classes.name: DltConfig
classes.note: This element defines a Dlt configuration for a specific Ecu.

dltEcu.note: Reference to the Ecu representation in the Log And Trace

dltLogChannel.note: Describes the DltLogChannels that are configured for the output

sessionId.note: This attribute defines whether the sessionId is used or

timestamp.note: This attribute defines whether a timestamp shall be added the Dlt messages or not.

classes.name: DltLogChannel
classes.note: This element contains the settings for the log/trace message output for a tuple of ApplicationId and ContextId (verbose mode) or a SessionId (non-verbose mode).

application.note: Reference to the Swc that produces the log or trace Please note that this reference shall not be set that the Bsw module produces the associated log messages.

defaultTrace.note: This attributes defines the default trace status.

dltMessage.note: Reference to DltMessages that can be transported over in the DltPdu. 2090 Document ID 63: AUTOSAR_CP_TPS_SystemTemplate R23-11

logChannelId.note: This attribute identifies the Channel for usage within the Trace protocol.

logTraceDefault.note: This attribute allows to set a log level Threshold for Log Level filtering.

nonVerbose.note: This attribute defines whether this channel supports Dlt messages. If disabled only verbose shall be used.

rxPduTriggering.note: Reference to DltPdu that is received by the DltLog

segmentation.note: If enabled, segmentation will be used if a DLT message is than Pdu.length referenced via DltLogChannel.tx

txPduTriggering.note: Reference to DltPdu that is transmitted by the DltLog
